-- Iran, Afghanistan to Cooperate on Tourism, Banking, Mehr Reports
-- B y   Y e g a n e h   S a l e h i
-- 2012-09-04T08:54:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-04/iran-afghanistan-to-cooperate-on-tourism-banking-mehr-reports.html
Iran and  Afghanistan  will sign a
memorandum of understanding for cooperation in trade, banking
and tourism, the state-run Mehr news agency  reported , without
saying where it got the information.  Iranian Foreign Minister  Ali Akbar Salehi  will travel to
Afghanistan later today to meet his Afghan counterpart, Zalmai Rassoul, and participate in the fourth Iran-Afghanistan economic
committee meeting, Mehr said, without providing details.  A group of 30 Iranian experts and deputies in Afghan
affairs will participate in the meeting, during which the
memorandum will be drafted.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yeganeh Salehi in Tehran at 
 yalehi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  